sub_item.synopsis: Two prep school teenagers create and sell imitations of Max and Caroline's cupcake T-shirts.
sub_item.series_synopsis: Street-wise Max (Kat Dennings) doesn't expect much from the new waitress at her night job, a rich girl who has reluctantly joined the food service industry after a string of bad luck. But to her surprise, Caroline (Beth Behrs) is a woman of substance and just may be her ticket to success. The two strike up an unlikely friendship after Caroline discovers that Max can bake a mean cupcake, and the women decide if they can just wrangle up the start-up cash, they may have found their big break. Their co-workers at the diner are boss Han Lee, cook Oleg and cashier Earl.
sub_item.title: 2 Broke Girls

sub_item.synopsis: Competitors face obstacles that include Salmon Ladder, Rumbling Dice and Clear Climb.
sub_item.series_synopsis: Competitors tackle the world's most difficult obstacle course.
sub_item.title: American Ninja Warrior

sub_item.display_title: So You Think You Can Dance
sub_item.synopsis: The top 20 perform for the judges; a special performer takes the stage.
sub_item.series_synopsis: Contestants compete to become America's best dancer.
sub_item.title: So You Think You Can Dance

sub_item.synopsis: An attorney (Jessica Hecht) defends a pedophile suspected of slaying a boy in Central Park.
sub_item.series_synopsis: Detectives who are part of the NYPD's Special Victims Unit investigate crimes against the vulnerable. While the focus of other shows in the "Law & Order" franchise is primarily on murder cases, the SVU detectives frequently deal with rape and assault, in which a survivor assists with the investigation. The series cast of veteran actors includes Mariska Hargitay and rapper Ice-T, and occasional crossover episodes feature detectives from other series including editions of the "Law & Order" franchise and as well as "Chicago PD," another series from the mind of executive producer Dick Wolf.
sub_item.title: Law & Order: Special Victims Unit

sub_item.synopsis: Rita no puede olvidar y con el paso de los años toma más fuerza para cobrar su propia venganza.
sub_item.series_synopsis: Abandonada em um lixão pela madrasta, a menina Rita jura vingança. Já adulta, ela assume a identidade de Nina e volta para se vingar da megera, mas se vê dividida ao descobrir que o seu grande amor é filho da mulher que arruinou a sua vida.
sub_item.title: Avenida Brasil

sub_item.synopsis: A Cuban immigrant from Castro's jails cuts a violent path of destruction on his way to the top of Miami's drug trade.
sub_item.title: Scarface

sub_item.synopsis: Eva Schloss shares her childhood memories of Holocaust victim Anne Frank.
sub_item.title: Anne Frank: Beyond the Diary

sub_item.synopsis: Pete builds a theraputic, butterfly-themed treehouse that includes six trees in Independence, Ohio.
sub_item.series_synopsis: People who know and work with Pete Nelson describe him as a tree whisperer. For his part, Nelson lets the trees do the talking. He's a world-renowned treehouse designer and builder, and this series documents the work he and his team of craftsmen -- including his son Charlie -- do to create incredible homes and businesses in nature's canopy. Pete uses a combination of science and art to realize clients' sky-high aspirations of magnificent multibedroom treehouses with elaborate kitchens and bathrooms, or simpler, peaceful one-room escapes. "We awaken that inner child who dreams of living among the trees," Pete says. One-of-a-kind above-ground spaces featured in the series include a spa retreat, a brewery, a honeymoon suite, an Irish-themed cottage, and an 800-square-foot Texas treehouse with a full bath and flat-screen TV.
sub_item.title: Treehouse Masters

sub_item.synopsis: In Detroit, a cunning serial killer (Matthew Fox) pushes young detective and psychologist Alex Cross (Tyler Perry) to his moral and psychological limits.
sub_item.title: Alex Cross

sub_item.synopsis: Cyborg, Beast Boy and Robin's vacation glow is interrupted; Raven's dark magic is overused.
sub_item.series_synopsis: This follow-up to the popular "Teen Titans" series takes a more comedic look at the superheroes, showing what life is like for the teens when their capes come off. Funny things happen to Robin, Starfire, Raven, Beast Boy and Cyborg between saving the world and being regular teens, living together without adult supervision. The teens, in their ordinary lives, deal with the everyday issues of adolescence that include such important things as having staring contests to determine who does the laundry and going on a series of quests to construct the perfect sandwich. But, of course, the heroes still fight crime in Jump City when the need arises. Whatever the situation, they're always ready for an adventure -- inside the house or out of it.
sub_item.title: Teen Titans Go!

sub_item.display_title: The Real Housewives of Orange County
sub_item.synopsis: Vicki gets a telephone call that changes her life; Shannon extends an olive branch to Meghan.
sub_item.series_synopsis: They may live in the lap of luxury, but life isn't always perfect for the women who reside in one of the wealthiest enclaves of the U.S. They continue to focus on living large; plastic surgery, working out, shopping, drinking, dancing, and dining out top their agendas. Ladies come and go through the show's run, with the 10th season's group featuring newcomer Meghan King Edmonds, the wife of former professional baseball player Jim Edmonds, who joins show veterans that include Vicki Gunvalson and Tamra Judge (previously known as Tamra Barney).
sub_item.title: The Real Housewives of Orange County

sub_item.synopsis: Buddhist monks pass through Arlen looking for a reincarnated lama.
sub_item.series_synopsis: Set in Texas, an animated series follows the life of propane salesman Hank Hill, who lives with his substitute-teacher wife Peggy, wannabe comedian son Bobby, and deadbeat niece Luanne. Hank has strikingly stereotypical views about God and country but is unpretentious and sees the world simply.
sub_item.title: King of the Hill

sub_item.synopsis: Shady concert promoters (Ice Cube, Mike Epps) get in over their heads with a big-name music act.
sub_item.title: The Janky Promoters

sub_item.synopsis: During a weekend trip to Mexico, three friends look for fun but find death instead when they run afoul of cultists who practice human sacrifice.
sub_item.title: Borderland
